# Data Questions and Stories


#### In lessons 5 and 6, students explore the art of crafting effective data-driven questions and learn how to tell compelling data stories, focusing on the clarity, relevance, and ethical implications of their inquiries while examining real-life examples to understand the elements of impactful data storytelling.

---

## Lesson 5: Effective Data Questions

<img src="https://images.code.org/f37f3e02d208df56ab9ee693170e03e4-image-1724342677390.png" alt="judicial scale icon" width="250px"  style="border-radius:10px; float:right; margin: 0 20px 0px 40px;">


#### In this lesson, students will explore how to derive insightful and meaningful questions from a provided dataset, utilizing established criteria to evaluate and refine their inquiries.
#### The lesson progresses through a systematic approach to understanding and applying key characteristics of effective questions.
#### Students will engage in hands-on activities to rank, refine, and ultimately formulate their own data-driven questions, with an emphasis on relevance, clarity, measurability, and ethical considerations.

